<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('./partials/head.ejs', {
    pageTitle: 'About BookLantern',
    pageDescription: 'Millions of free and public-domain books—one clean reader. Built on open libraries.'
  }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/site.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('./partials/navbar.ejs') %>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner fade-in">
      <h1>About BookLantern</h1>
      <p>
        BookLantern brings together results from <strong>Internet Archive</strong>, <strong>Open Library</strong>,
        and <strong>Project Gutenberg</strong> so you can discover <strong>millions of free and public-domain books</strong>
        in one place—then read them in a clean, unified reader.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn" href="/read">Browse Books</a>
        <a class="btn alt" href="/watch">Explore Videos</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Value strip with simple numbers -->
  <section class="value-strip">
    <div class="container value-inner">
      <div class="value-item">
        <div class="vi-title">Millions+ titles</div>
        <div class="vi-copy">Search across vast public-domain and free-to-read catalogs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item">
        <div class="vi-title">3 open libraries</div>
        <div class="vi-copy">Internet Archive, Open Library, and Project Gutenberg—one search.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item">
        <div class="vi-title">One clean reader</div>
        <div class="vi-copy">Distraction-free pagination, bookmarks, and a consistent reading flow.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="shelf-header">
        <h2>Our mission</h2>
        <div class="hint">Access + delight</div>
      </div>
      <p style="max-width:800px">
        We don’t try to be yet another library. Instead, we make the open stacks easy to search and
        <em>delightful</em> to read. Results link back to the original sources and respect their availability.
        Where possible, we open books right inside BookLantern so you can stay focused on the text.
      </p>
      <p style="max-width:800px">
        Have suggestions or want to help? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a>. If you’d like to support the
        source libraries, consider donating to Internet Archive, Open Library, or Project Gutenberg.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> BookLantern • Built on open libraries • <a href="/read">Start reading</a>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
